    "discriminators": [
     "Same rhythmic morphology as DOORKnck — a periodic train of 2-4 sharp impulses — but struck on GLASS. The pane rings: the centroid sits near 2.5-3 kHz with a bright ~0.2 s rattle, where a wooden door knock sits near 1.2 kHz and dies in ~0.1 s. That spectral offset is the only measurable separation, hence narrowable, not separable.",
     "Against WNDWHdwr: a knock excites the pane and is periodic; latch clicks are aperiodic and metal-only.",
     "A tap that shatters the pane is a GLASS break, not WNDWKnck: burst morphology plus a dense high-frequency debris texture tail."
    ],
